# ${TAG}

## Install

**Download:** [`stremio-addarr-install.tar.gz`](https://github.com/${REPO}/releases/download/${TAG}/stremio-addarr-install.tar.gz)
**Checksum:** [`stremio-addarr-install.tar.gz.sha256`](https://github.com/${REPO}/releases/download/${TAG}/stremio-addarr-install.tar.gz.sha256)

---

## Quick Raspberry Pi install

```bash
# Authenticate if you haven't already (required for private repos)
gh auth login

# Download the release assets
gh release download --repo ${REPO} --tag ${TAG} --pattern 'stremio-addarr-install.tar.gz*'
```

**Public repo / anonymous download only** (will fail on private repos):
```bash
curl -fL --retry 3 -o stremio-addarr-install.tar.gz \
  https://github.com/${REPO}/releases/download/${TAG}/stremio-addarr-install.tar.gz
curl -fL --retry 3 -o stremio-addarr-install.tar.gz.sha256 \
  https://github.com/${REPO}/releases/download/${TAG}/stremio-addarr-install.tar.gz.sha256
```

> ⚠️ If `file stremio-addarr-install.tar.gz` shows `ASCII text` or `tar` fails with `not in gzip format`,
> the download returned an error page. Check the URL, release, or repo access and use `gh release download` instead.

```bash
# Optional: verify checksum
sha256sum -c stremio-addarr-install.tar.gz.sha256

# Sanity-check before extraction
file stremio-addarr-install.tar.gz | grep -q 'gzip' \
  || { echo "ERROR: Downloaded file is not a valid gzip archive. Check the URL, release, or repo access."; exit 1; }

# Extract to /opt/stremio-addarr (files owned by pi)
sudo mkdir -p /opt/stremio-addarr
sudo tar -xzf stremio-addarr-install.tar.gz -C /opt/stremio-addarr --strip-components=1
sudo chown -R pi:pi /opt/stremio-addarr

# Install production dependencies
cd /opt/stremio-addarr
npm ci --omit=dev

# Configure
cp .env.example .env && nano .env

# Install and start systemd service
sudo cp deploy/stremio-addarr.service.example /etc/systemd/system/stremio-addarr.service
sudo systemctl daemon-reload && sudo systemctl enable --now stremio-addarr
```

> Replace `pi` with your actual service account username if different.
> See [README.md](https://github.com/${REPO}/blob/${TAG}/README.md) for the full setup guide.

